ðŸ“‹ Working Principle
The LDR and 10kÎ© resistor form a voltage divider connected to analog pin A0.
The analog value changes depending on light falling on the LDR.
If light is below a set threshold (e.g. less than 500), the LED turns ON.
The LCD displays the light intensity in real time.

